<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-06-15T17:00:00-05:00" n="163" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d163">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">340.1115A/868: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Genoa</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Balch</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-15T18:00:00-04:00">June
                                        15, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>162. Your 83 [<hi rend="italic">82</hi>], June 12, 7 p.m. Americans
                                in Mediterranean area have remained there despite warning they
                                should leave while there was time and the Government cannot now
                                undertake to send additional American shipping for them into the
                                dangerous combat zone.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>